description: {"blocks":[{"key":"2j4d3","text":"This protocol describes the qualitative determination of IgG antibodies against the nucleocapsid (N) protein of SARS-CoV-2 in serum from domestic dogs and cats, the indirect ELISA (Enzyme-Linked Immunosorbent Assay) kit ID Screen® SARS-CoV-2 Double Antigen Multi-Species (IDvet, Grabels, France). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d8vmv","text":"The diagnostic kit detects antibodies against the nucleocapsid (N protein) of the SARS-CoV-2 virus. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cqp93","text":"This test can be used on samples from dogs, cats, mink, ferrets, cattle, sheep, goats, horses and any other susceptible species requiring serum, plasma or whole blood samples.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"8irl4","text":"Collect the serum, plasma or whole blood samples from dogs, cats, mink, ferrets, cattle, sheep, goats, horses and any other susceptible species.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d3b5a","text":"Allow the reagents to reach room temperature (21 °C ± 5 °C) before use. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9d6fb","text":"Homogenize all reagents and serum samples by immersion or vortexing.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5njgr","text":"Add 25 µL of Diluent 13 to the remaining wells.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ct2hb","text":"Add 25 µL of the serum samples, which previously had been homogenized by vortexing, to the remaining wells (Figure 1).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ctpoa","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fl7fh","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"cu4h","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"59A6E4F03F6511ED852FC745E0221D05","height":343,"id":298841,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"fdotd","text":"Figure 1. Addition of Diluent 13.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}},"mime":"image/png","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"Imagen 1.png","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jd45bqwaf.jpg","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jd43bqwaf.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jd44bqwaf.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jd42bqwaf.webp","width":293}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"43r23","text":"Cover the plate and incubate for 45 minutes ± 5 minutes at 37 °C ( ± 2°C).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"u7e8","text":"Empty the wells and wash each well 5 times with at least 300 µL of wash solution, avoid drying the wells between washes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"592sd","text":"Prepare the 1X conjugate by diluting the 10X conjugate 1:10 with diluent 13.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"2hfcv","text":"Add 100 µL of the 1X conjugate to each well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"6lqv","text":"Cover the plate and incubate for 30 minutes at 21°C (± 5°C).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9qqp8","text":"Add at least 300 µL of wash solution so that this substrate reacts with the secondary antibody enzyme and provides a visible signal that can be quantified.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7ljs3","text":"In the presence of antibodies, a blue coloration should appear (Figure 2), avoid drying of the wells between washes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fevua","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"de35m","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"823547903F6511ED852FC745E0221D05","height":222,"id":298845,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[{"length":10,"offset":0,"style":"bold"}],"key":"6coqp","text":"Figure 2. Substrate reaction in the presence of antibodies.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}},"mime":"image/png","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"Imagen 2.png","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jd49bqwaf.jpg","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jd47bqwaf.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jd48bqwaf.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jd46bqwaf.webp","width":312}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"50gj5","text":" Cover the plate and incubate 20 min ± 2 min at 21°C (± 5°C) in the dark.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6f0jn","text":"Add 100 µL of stop solution to each well in order to stop the substrate reaction (Figure 3).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9bp3g","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"18l97","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"9AAAE0503F6511ED852FC745E0221D05","height":241,"id":298849,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[{"length":10,"offset":0,"style":"bold"}],"key":"6okc5","text":"Figure 3. Stop reaction","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}},"mime":"image/png","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"Imagen 3.png","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jd5dbqwaf.jpg","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jd5bbqwaf.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jd5cbqwaf.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jd5abqwaf.webp","width":224}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7ad4g","text":"Finally, the optical density (OD) is read in a Cytation 3 multimodal microplate reader (BioTek Instruments, Inc. Winooski, VT, USA) using a wavelength of 450 nm.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"deu2","text":"The assay is validated if:","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3ubp1","text":"","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7o73o","text":"- The mean value of the Positive Control O.D. (DOcp) is greater than 0.350.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bpive","text":"","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5db6e","text":"DOcp \u003e 0.350","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d8197","text":"","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4uacr","text":"- The ratio of the mean of the optical density values of the positive and negative controls (DOcp and DOcn) is greater than 3.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e4elj","text":"","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bvjtn","text":"DOcp/DOcn \u003e 3","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3h1g3","text":"After the laboratory reading, the sample/positive control (S/P) ratio was calculated with the data obtained, which was expressed as a percentage, using the following formula:","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"244jm","text":"","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6c1m6","text":"Samples presenting a S/P%:","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"24acj","text":"","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"33sg","text":"- Less than or equal to 50% are considered negative.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"berks","text":"- Between 50% and 60% are considered doubtful.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5ahdo","text":"- Greater than or equal to 60% are considered positive.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"528c5","text":"","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9eb6i","text":"Results Status","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f0cmc","text":"S/P % ≤ 50 % Negative","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d9gs","text":"50 % \u003c S/P % \u003c 60% Doubtful","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1qsr8","text":"S/P % ≥ 60 % Positive","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"qap7","text":"Add 100 µL of the developing solution into each well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bnc7v","text":"Add 25 µL of Negative control to wells A1 and A2 and 25 µL of Positive control to wells A3 and A4.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"a0cqg","text":"Empty the wells. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
